A ferry disaster off the coast of Java left hundreds missing as rough weather hindered rescue efforts.
Survivors were found drifting at sea, with some rescued by fishermen after days on life rafts.
The Senopati Nusantara sank quickly after being pounded by heavy waves during a journey from Borneo to Java.
Despite bloated bodies washing ashore, rescuers remained hopeful, dropping supplies to survivors.
Weeping relatives awaited news at a local hospital, while search teams scoured the seas for the missing passengers.
The tragic incident highlighted the dangers of sea travel in Indonesia's stormy waters.
